race.comment: CRUSADER KINGS (2) shouldered 61kgs and did a great job to plough through the mud and get up for second last start over 1280m at Orange. Drops 5kgs and with the help of the inside gate is ready for a first tilt at this distance. TOM VEGAS (5) caught the eye first-up over 1318m at Dubbo then was ridden forward and couldn't maintain the pressure over 1500m in a Rosehill Highway last time. Cherry ripe and can improve in today's more appealing set up. HANNAH'S BRIDGE (12) won two on the trot then raced just off the speed and boxed on okay to finish alongside TOM VEGAS in a Rosehill Highway recently. Light weight chance but does need some breaks from a wide draw. TURNED DOWN (6) made progress last start when in the money over 1300m at Kembla. Should be peaking at the third run back. ZARIZATYCOON (1) is back after an 11-month spell. The winner of five from eight including three at this trip. Trialling extremely well and will be fully wound up for this.
